## [ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS] — NEVER DO THESE

1. NEVER use `ethers.js` or `web3.js` — Viem is the ONLY EVM standard
2. NEVER use global singletons — factory function pattern ONLY
3. NEVER `console.log` in production paths — use structured logger only
4. NEVER commit secrets, private keys, or API keys in code
5. NEVER skip Shadow simulation before Dispatcher broadcast
6. NEVER mark an Extraction Lane as "Settled" without post-strike balance verification
7. NEVER use a single account for multiple concurrent lanes without Nonce-Manager
8. NEVER catch errors silently — every catch MUST log + emit LegionError typed event
9. NEVER use `any` TypeScript type in @packages/core — strict types only
10. NEVER write synchronous blocking code in hot paths — async/await or Piscina workers
11. NEVER use generic HTTP clients (axios/node-fetch) in @packages/core — use `undici`
12. NEVER implement liquidity routing without checking honeypot status first
13. NEVER process Fee-on-Transfer or Rebase tokens with standard ERC-20 transfer logic
14. NEVER submit a Flashbots bundle without `eth_callBundle` simulation first
15. NEVER accept a swap quote older than 30 seconds — always re-fetch

