## [MANDATORY PATTERNS] — ALWAYS DO THESE

### Architecture
- Every module exports a factory function: `createXxx(config)` — no `new Xxx()`
- Every async function returns `Promise<Result<T, LegionError>>` — never throws raw
- Every Sentinel function maps to exactly one entry in the Sentinel Matrix table
- Read `@docs/research/<relevant>.md` BEFORE writing any integration code
- Read `@docs/skills/<relevant>.md` BEFORE writing any performance/stealth/resilience code

### Performance (Skill: 01-concurrency)
- CPU-bound work → Piscina worker pool, never in main thread
- HTTP calls → `undici` with connection pooling, never one-shot fetch
- JSON serialization in hot paths → `fast-json-stringify` with compiled schema
- Telemetry batch processing → worker threads, target <50ms p99

### Stealth (Skill: 02-stealth)
- All RPC calls through proxy mesh — never direct IP
- TLS fingerprint rotation on every session using `tls-client` patterns
- User-Agent and header randomization on every request
- Rate limiting: respect per-chain RPC limits, add jitter to all retry delays

### EVM Simulation (Skill: 03-evm-math)
- Tenderly `eth_callBundle` OR Viem `publicClient.call()` MANDATORY before any broadcast
- Gas estimation: use simulation result + 20% buffer, never `estimateGas` alone
- solady-style math for all BigInt arithmetic — no floating point in wei calculations

### MEV & Bundles (Skill: 04-mev-bundles)
- Flashbots: always auth signer ≠ execution signer
- Bundle retry: max 5 blocks, re-sign with updated nonce each retry
- Jito (Solana): use tip account + bundle, never raw sendTransaction for MEV

### Token Safety (Skill: 05-honeypot + 07-nonstandard)
- EVERY token must pass honeypot check BEFORE Gatekeeper approval
- Fee-on-Transfer: use `balanceOf` delta check, not transfer return value
- ERC-777: register receiver hook OR use SafeERC20 wrapper
- Rebase tokens: snapshot share price before and after transfer

### Liquidity (Skill: 06-liquidity-pathfinding)
- Dual-quote: 1inch + ParaSwap → pick better `destAmount`
- Max price impact: 3% hard cap — Gatekeeper rejects above this
- Route must be validated on-chain via simulation, not just API response

### TX Resilience (Skill: 08-tx-resilience)
- Stuck tx detection: monitor mempool, auto-RBF after 30 seconds
- Nonce management: ALWAYS use centralized NonceManager from `@packages/core/nonce`
- Idempotency: every Extraction Lane has a unique `laneId` — check Redis before re-run
- Circuit breaker: if error rate >5% in 60s window → freeze all lanes

### Ghost-Fail Prevention (Skill: 09-ghost-fail-hardening)
- After EVERY sendTransaction: verify balance changed via `publicClient.getBalance`
- If balance unchanged after 2 confirmations → emit `GHOST_FAIL` event, abort lane
- Post-strike verification is NOT optional — it is the final gate

