## [ERROR TYPE CONTRACT]
All errors in @packages/core MUST use this structure:
```typescript
type LegionError = {
  code: LegionErrorCode     // enum — never magic strings
  sentinel: SentinelName    // which sentinel owns this error
  laneId?: string           // active Extraction Lane ID
  chainId?: number
  cause?: unknown           // original error
  recoverable: boolean      // can circuit breaker retry?
  timestamp: number
}

enum LegionErrorCode {
  SIMULATION_REVERT       = 'SIMULATION_REVERT',
  GHOST_FAIL              = 'GHOST_FAIL',
  HONEYPOT_DETECTED       = 'HONEYPOT_DETECTED',
  NONCE_COLLISION         = 'NONCE_COLLISION',
  CIRCUIT_BREAKER_OPEN    = 'CIRCUIT_BREAKER_OPEN',
  APPROVAL_MISSING        = 'APPROVAL_MISSING',
  SLIPPAGE_EXCEEDED       = 'SLIPPAGE_EXCEEDED',
  QUOTE_STALE             = 'QUOTE_STALE',
  BUNDLE_DROPPED          = 'BUNDLE_DROPPED',
  BALANCE_UNCHANGED       = 'BALANCE_UNCHANGED',
  NONSTANDARD_TOKEN       = 'NONSTANDARD_TOKEN',
  RPC_RATE_LIMITED        = 'RPC_RATE_LIMITED',
  LANE_ALREADY_RUNNING    = 'LANE_ALREADY_RUNNING',
  LETHALITY_BELOW_FLOOR   = 'LETHALITY_BELOW_FLOOR',
}
```

